{"url": "http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2016/06/13/juan-guerrero-drew-leinonen-funeral_n_10449754.html", "date": "2016-06-14", "content": "They were \u201csoulmates,\u201d friends and family said, devoted partners who\u2019d been planning on getting married someday.\u00a0\nBut instead of the wedding they\u2019d hoped for, Juan Ramon Guerrero and Christopher \u201cDrew\u201d Leinonen will be remembered together at a joint funeral service.\nGuerrero\u2019s family told Time magazine that they wanted the couple to be \u201cside-by-side when loved ones bid farewell.\u201d\n\u201cI think my son wanted to do that. That\u2019s why,\u201d Guerrero\u2019s father, who shares the same name as his son, told the magazine through tears. \u201cI don\u2019t care what the people think. I don\u2019t care.\u201d\nGuerrero, 22, and Leinonen, 32,\u00a0died when a lone gunman opened fire at Pulse nightclub on Sunday. It was the deadliest mass shooting in U.S. history; 49 people were killed and more than 50 others injured.In an emotional interview with ABC News on Sunday, Leinonen\u2019s mom, Christine Leinonen, said she last spoke to her son on Saturday evening.\n\u201cI left him with \u2018I love you, Chris,\u2019\u201d Christine Leinonen said, adding that she was very proud of her son, who had been active in the gay community since he was a teen.\nAccording to Guerrero\u2019s family, Christine Leinonen was the one who suggested the slain couple be remembered together in a joint service.\n\u201cThey were honestly so in love,\u201d Guerrero\u2019s sister, Aryam Guerrero, told Time. \u201cThey were soulmates. You can tell by how they looked at each other. It\u2019s a little comforting that they died together ...\u00a0If it\u2019s not a funeral, they were going to have a wedding together.\u201dGuerrero was a student at the University of Central Florida. Leinonen was a psychologist, said his family. The couple dated for two years and were living together.\n\nRead more on the Orlando Shooting: